	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />That's one thing that's potentially confusing right from the start: what is often referred to as the SNES header is the embedded information at $7FC0/$FFC0. What's a good name for it? It's not a header, since it's not at the head of the file.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


